Package com.bluegosling.collections.lists

New interfaces and implementations related to the standard Java List interface.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AssociativeList<E,K>
    A List that can have associative keys and can be viewed as a Map.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayBackedLinkedList<E>
    A list implementation that attempts to achieve some of the benefits of a linked list without sacrificing the overwhelming performance advantages and memory efficiency of arrays.
    AssociativeArrayList<E,K>
    An ArrayList that is also an AssociativeList.
    TreeList<E>
    A list structure that is stored as a binary tree.
    UnrolledLinkedList<E>
    A list implementation that is a hybrid between a linked list and an array.
